# Launch configuration

Every launch = the **same fields**, whether console or API.

## The eight you set

- **AMI** — OS image
- **Instance type** — CPU + memory (`m7g.large`)
- **Key pair** — SSH / Windows password
- **Network** — VPC, subnet, public-IP toggle
- **Security group** — instance firewall
- **Storage** — root EBS + extra volumes
- **IAM role** — via an **instance profile**
- **User data** — boot script, run **once**

## Two to get right

**IAM role, not access keys** — the metadata service vends rotating creds, so nothing sits on disk. **User data** = first-boot automation (install, pull code, register).
